The Inkatha Freedom Party (IFP) has officially announced its newly-elected provincial leadership after holding its first provincial conference since 2011. Nkandla Mayor, Thami Ntuli, who was nominated by national IFP leader Prince Mangosuthu Buthelezi, has been announced as the provincial chairperson. The position was contested by Mbangiseni Yengwa and Ntuli. “This conference is a lead-up to the IFP’s National General Conference that will be held on the 23rd to 25th of August upon which the party will have a new leader for the first time since it was founded in 1975,” says IFP Secretary-General Velenkosini Hlabisa. Watch a related video below: 